	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Sep</p>
			<p class="post-day">25</p>
			<p class="post-year">2006</p>				
		</div>

		The FCC is apparently planning to adopt a Notice of Inquiry (NOI) seeking comment on network neutrality. An NOI is an informational proceeding, in which the agency asks questions but doesn&#8217;t propose any rules. I&#8217;m concerned that this is an attempt to dissipate some of the pressure for nondiscrimination rules, which is now focused on Congress. I actually think the FCC would be the better place to address Net Neutrality ...
		
	</div>

