			<p class="post-month">Sep</p>
			<p class="post-day">22</p>
			<p class="post-year">2006</p>				
		</div>

		OneWebDay is a global celebration of the Web and its importance to our lives. The first one is being held today in dozens of locations around the world. My friend Susan Crawford is one of the organizers, and deserves a great deal of credit for kicking off an important, decentralized effort. It&#8217;s worth being reminded from time to time that The Web is People.
		
