		Senator Stevens says that gridlock over network neutrality may derail passage of comprehensive telecom reform legislation this year. It&#8217;s remarkable that the net neutrality issue has gotten such traction in such a short period of time, especially given how little public and industry interest there was for a long time. Though it&#8217;s not widely appreciated, the battle over what is now called network neutrality started in 1998, and the outcome ...
		
